<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5903&amp;p=54714#p54714"><![CDATA[
Is the CHR-ROM write-protected on the PowerPak?  If it's not, that would cause the effect you're seeing.  But at the same time, the bad writes can end up in the nametables, attributes, and possibly the palette.<br /><br />Yeah could be a bad cart connection too, but that's less likely on a Famicom and easy to rule out.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Mon Jan 04, 2010 1:35 pm</p><hr />
