Sounds less like "CHR ROM corruption" and more like the PPU doing something "unexpected" as a result of doing too much in a single frame (single NMI/interrupt).  You might have to resort to cycle counting to see how much time your NMI routine takes up...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">koitsu</a> — Mon Jan 04, 2010 1:47 am</p><hr />
